article.description: DeWayne Russell had 21 points, nine assists and four rebounds and Grand Canyon beat San Diego State 76-72 in a frantic finish on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Russell, Grand Canyon hold of San Diego St. 76-72
article.linkText: Russell, Grand Canyon hold of San Diego St. 76-72
article.story: PHOENIX -- DeWayne Russell had 21 points, nine assists and four rebounds and Grand Canyon beat San Diego State 76-72 in a frantic finish on Wednesday night. Trailing 74-72 with 10 seconds left, San Diego State's Jeremy Hemsley attempted to split a double team but Fiifi Aidoo stole the ball for a layup and the game's final margin. DeWayne Russell's jumper with 12:47 to play gave Grand Canyon (4-4) a 55-44 lead but the Aztecs only needed a couple of minutes to go on an 11-0 run to knot the game. Zylan Cheatham made a layup and a pair of free throws, Hemsley hit a pair of 3s, and Valentine Izundu added a free throw during the run. Hemsley scored 28 points and Zylam Cheatham added 17 points and 12 boards for San Diego State (4-3). The Lopes' bench outscored San Diego State's 24-6 and collected 13 fast break points to just five for the Aztecs.
